<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="508" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,541,1720]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,613,639]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Description:</emphasis>
Mature Larva: Body length 
<quantity box="[673,778,613,640]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" unit="mm" value="12.5">12.5 mm</quantity>
; length of cerci 
<quantity box="[963,1053,613,640]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
. Body brown with pale yellowish maculae (
<figureCitation box="[260,344,649,676]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,541,1720]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,685,711]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Head:</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[365,453,685,712]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[534,623,685,711]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
; pale brown (
<figureCitation box="[774,858,685,712]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
); without conspicuous markings, antennae short 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
; subquadrangular; anterior and lateral margins convex, with rows of dense hair-like simple setae directed anteriorly and medially; posterior margin slightly concave. Compound eyes black. Antennal scapes and pedicels pale brown, flagella pale. Labrum 
<quantity box="[490,577,793,819]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" unit="mm" value="7.8">7.8 mm</quantity>
in width; dark brown with a rectangular mesal emargination; long hair-like setae on lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[427,512,829,856]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
). Hypopharynx as in 
<figureCitation box="[758,842,829,856]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
. Mandible without scattered setae along molar area; incisors serrated; outer incisor longer than inner incisor (
<figureCitation box="[781,865,865,892]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
). Maxilla as in 
<figureCitation box="[1035,1117,865,892]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
. Labium broad, glossae with narrow basal separation, subtriangular; paraglossae slightly expanded laterally; apical segment of palp pointed, dorsal surface with dense row of comb setae (
<figureCitation box="[663,748,937,964]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–67" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[162,1429,186,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[158,1429,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–67. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 58. Labium; 59. Foreleg; 60. Dorsal surface of forefemur; 61. Midleg; 62. Hindleg; 63. Claw; 64. Gill I; 65. Gill III; 66. Gill V; 67. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042540/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,541,1720]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,973,999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Thorax:</emphasis>
Pronotum pale brown without dark marks (
<figureCitation box="[784,868,973,1000]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Legs (
<figureCitation box="[956,1088,973,1000]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–67" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[162,1429,186,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[158,1429,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–67. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 58. Labium; 59. Foreleg; 60. Dorsal surface of forefemur; 61. Midleg; 62. Hindleg; 63. Claw; 64. Gill I; 65. Gill III; 66. Gill V; 67. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042540/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Figs 59–62</figureCitation>
): dark brown with pale yellowish; dorsal surface of femur with hypodermal spots on middle and apex with small stout and ovate scattered setae on dorsal surface; femora of all legs with row of long hair-like setae on outer margin, apex of femora with blunt apical projection; (
<figureCitation box="[288,373,1081,1108]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–67" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[162,1429,186,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[158,1429,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–67. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 58. Labium; 59. Foreleg; 60. Dorsal surface of forefemur; 61. Midleg; 62. Hindleg; 63. Claw; 64. Gill I; 65. Gill III; 66. Gill V; 67. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042540/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
); tibiae long, brownish yellow, tarsi yellowish with basal dark brown. Claw with 5–6 denticles (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,1117,1144]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–67" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[162,1429,186,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[158,1429,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–67. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 58. Labium; 59. Foreleg; 60. Dorsal surface of forefemur; 61. Midleg; 62. Hindleg; 63. Claw; 64. Gill I; 65. Gill III; 66. Gill V; 67. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042540/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,541,1720]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1153,1179]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Abdominal terga pale brown, abdominal terga II–IX each with single, prominent, acute median spine (
<figureCitation box="[226,311,1189,1216]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of abdominal terga I–X each with row of small spines (
<figureCitation box="[1147,1231,1189,1216]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
); segments II–VII with small posterolateral extensions (
<figureCitation box="[572,656,1225,1252]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
); terga I–V medially dark brown, terga VI–VII with submedian pale spot and segment VIII and IX brown; tergum X anteriorly pale and posteriorly brown (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1212,1261,1288]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
); sterna pale yellow without markings (
<figureCitation box="[364,447,1297,1324]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). Lamellae of gill I somewhat extended beneath of abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1227,1297,1324]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–67" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[162,1429,186,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[158,1429,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–67. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 58. Labium; 59. Foreleg; 60. Dorsal surface of forefemur; 61. Midleg; 62. Hindleg; 63. Claw; 64. Gill I; 65. Gill III; 66. Gill V; 67. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042540/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
). Gills II–VII with anal ribs on margin (
<figureCitation box="[382,513,1333,1360]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–67" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[162,1429,186,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[158,1429,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–67. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 58. Labium; 59. Foreleg; 60. Dorsal surface of forefemur; 61. Midleg; 62. Hindleg; 63. Claw; 64. Gill I; 65. Gill III; 66. Gill V; 67. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042540/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Figs 65–67</figureCitation>
). Cerci with row of hair-like setae dorsally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="508" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,541,1720]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1369,1395]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The larva of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1980" box="[484,771,1369,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unispinosus" subGenus="Epeorus">
<emphasis box="[484,577,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Epeorus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[596,621,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">E.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[639,771,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">unispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from other species by the following combination of characters: (i) abdominal terga II–IX each with single, prominent, acute median spine and without lateral spines fringing the posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[655,788,1441,1468]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Figs 50–53</figureCitation>
); (ii) anterior margin of labrum with a rectangular mesal emargination (
<figureCitation box="[314,398,1477,1504]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,182,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[185,1401,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–57. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 50. Dorsal view; 51. Abdomen ventral view; 52. Closer view of abdomen; 53. Closer view of abdominal terga V; 54. Labrum; 55. Hypopharynx; 56. Mandible; 57. Maxilla." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042538/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
); and (iii) gill I slightly expanded anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[905,989,1477,1504]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–67" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[162,1429,186,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[158,1429,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–67. Larva of Epeorus (Epeorus) unispinosus 58. Labium; 59. Foreleg; 60. Dorsal surface of forefemur; 61. Midleg; 62. Hindleg; 63. Claw; 64. Gill I; 65. Gill III; 66. Gill V; 67. Gill VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042540/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,972,1513,1540]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,541,1720]" box="[199,972,1513,1540]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,1513,1539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[362,429,1513,1539]" name="Nepal" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[483,541,1513,1539]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">India</collectingCountry>
(Tawang district, 
<collectingRegion box="[742,960,1513,1540]" country="India" name="Arunachal Pradesh" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Arunachal Pradesh</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="508" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,541,1720]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1549,1575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Remarks:</emphasis>
Way back in 1955, Ueno briefly described an imperfectly preserved larva collected during Japanese- 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,1585,1611]" name="Nepal" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Nepal</collectingCountry>
Himalaya Expedition but did not provide formal species name. 
<bibRefCitation author="Braasch, D." box="[926,1097,1585,1611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" pagination="55 - 65" refId="ref9851" refString="Braasch, D. (1980) Eintagsfliegen (Gattungen Epeorus und Iron) aus Nepal (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae). Reichenbachia, 18, 55 - 65." type="journal article" year="1980">Braasch (1980)</bibRefCitation>
slightly improved the description and named it as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1980" box="[394,628,1622,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unispinosus">
<emphasis box="[394,628,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Epeorus unispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Present larval description is in conformity with that if 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1980" box="[1271,1436,1622,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unispinosus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1436,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">E. unispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[440,507,1657,1683]" name="Nepal" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and its distribution is extended herein to 
<collectingRegion box="[961,1229,1657,1683]" country="India" name="Arunachal Pradesh" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Arunachal Pradesh state</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[1265,1326,1657,1683]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">India</collectingCountry>
. It has the salient features of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1881" box="[510,603,1694,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[510,603,1694,1719]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="508">Epeorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[610,646,1693,1719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="508" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as pointed out by Kluge (personal communication).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
